In [93]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

#       
features = train_df.columns
for feature in features:
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.hist(train_df[feature], bins=30, alpha=0.5, label='Train', color='blue')
    plt.hist(valid_df[feature], bins=30, alpha=0.5, label='Validation', color='orange')
    plt.title(f'Distribution of {feature}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()

In [97]:
from scipy.stats import ks_2samp

for column in train_df.columns:
    stat, p_value = ks_2samp(train_df[column], valid_df[column])
    print(f"{column}: KS-statistic={stat:.4f}, p-value={p_value:.4f}")
